President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate several individuals for various positions. David B. Barlow of Utah has been nominated to serve as a Judge on the U.S. District Court for the District of Utah. Barlow is currently a partner at Dorsey & Whitney LLP, focusing on civil litigation and white-collar investigations. Robert A. Molloy of the Virgin Islands has been nominated to serve as a Judge on the U.S. District Court for the U.S. Virgin Islands. Molloy is currently a Judge on the Superior Court of the Virgin Islands. Kevin R. Sweazea of New Mexico has been nominated to serve as a Judge on the U.S. District Court for the District of New Mexico. Sweazea is currently a Magistrate Judge on the U.S. District Court for the District of New Mexico. Fernando L.G. Sablan of Guam has been nominated to serve as U.S. Marshal for Guam and the Commonwealth of Northern Mariana Islands. Sablan is a former officer for the United States Customs and Border Protection in Guam.